    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-06T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-06T03:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <head>426. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Consulate General at
                        Jerusalem</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d426fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.85/7–656. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Received at 6:31 a.m. Also sent to Amman, Cairo, Damascus, Beirut, and Tel
                        Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-06T11:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1956—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Reference: Department telegram 3.<note n="2" xml:id="d426fn2">Telegram 3 to
                        Jerusalem, July 5, requested information concerning troop movements on the
                        Jordanian–Israeli frontier. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi>
                        684A.85/7–556)</note> At 1000 zone time (0800 <gloss target="#t_GMT1"
                        >GMT</gloss>) July 6 <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName>
                    confirmed substance Consulate Telegram 4<note n="3" xml:id="d426fn3">Telegram 4
                        from Jerusalem, July 5, reported that rumors of Israeli troops massing on
                        the Jordanian border were false. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note> that
                    no Israeli troop massing and no military action Jordan border has taken
                    place.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName> believes origin unfounded rumor
                    was his warning to <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> and Nuwwar July
                    2 of <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName>’s threat of retaliation
                    Jordan border incidents. He opines his warning magnified in transmission from
                        <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> via Arab Ambassadors to Arab
                    Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">Sabini</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
